# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# shared-heart.form — the SHARED SHAPE of the great wisdom traditions as one
#   binary + language packs: five teachings that recur across six traditions,
#   each witnessed in every tradition's own voice. The model is numeric (the
#   lattice of which expression belongs to which teaching and tradition); every
#   word arrives as a pack — any tongue, and any tradition's OWN authored voice,
#   is a file, never a rebuild. The honesty line rides in every rendering.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Urs: "the core religions — can we boil it down to a shared binary shape and a
# language pack for most common languages."
#
# What this is, held in lanes (the resonance discipline):
#   INFERENCE — the recurring shapes are the comparative-reading inference (the
#     well-witnessed golden-rule table and its siblings), not a measured claim.
#   EVIDENCE — each expression paraphrases a widely-known teaching of its
#     tradition (Mahabharata, Dhammapada, Hillel, the gospels, hadith, the Tao
#     Te Ching and its kin); the pack lines stay close to those sources.
#   MYSTERY — what the teachings point AT is not in the model; the model holds
#     only the shape of the pointing.
#   SOVEREIGNTY — nothing about any tradition is baked in code (the band proves
#     the C is tradition-free); a community renders its own voice by authoring
#     its own pack. The pack IS the sovereignty mechanism.
#   HONESTY IN THE ARTIFACT — pack line 42 renders at the end of every output:
#     "these are shapes that recur across the traditions — each tradition is a
#     living whole, more than what is shared."

(shared-heart

  (lineage
    (over          numeric-core-symbol-pack.form)     # identity numeric, words removable
    (sibling-of    protocol-beliefs.form)              # the same carrier, the body's own protocols
    (pattern       self-translate-universal.fk)        # the runtime pack door
    (recipe        form-stdlib/shared-heart.fk)        # fsh-emit — quoteless, three-way clean
    (proof-band    tests/shared-heart-band.fk)         # 31 three-way
    (witness       scripts/shared_heart_demo.sh))      # English, Spanish, German from one model

  # ── The lattice ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (teachings   "the golden rule · compassion · presence-stillness · letting-go · unity")
  (traditions  "Hinduism · Buddhism · Judaism · Christianity · Islam · Taoism")
  (model       "30 rows (pack-line, teaching, tradition) — generated by the recipe,
                not hand-typed; the lattice structure IS the recipe")
  (completeness "every teaching carries an expression in EVERY tradition — the
                completeness of the lattice is the structural claim, and the band
                proves it from the model data (6 per teaching, 5 per tradition)")

  # ── The packs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (packs
    (shipped     "English, Spanish, German — written in the demo as the seed")
    (any-tongue  "a further language is a 42-line file; the binary needs no rebuild")
    (own-voice   "a tradition's community can author its own pack — its names, its
                  phrasings, its preferred renderings; the numeric core is silent
                  about all of it; this is the deepest reason the words live in
                  the pack and not the binary")
    (most-common "Mandarin, Hindi, Arabic, Bengali, Portuguese, Russian, French …
                  are pack files awaiting fluent authors — named, not pretended"))

  # ── Why one binary ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # The render makes the shared shape VISIBLE: six traditions speaking one
  # teaching side by side. The claim is carried by the structure, not by any
  # commentary — the reader sees the recurrence directly, in their own tongue,
  # with the honesty line closing every rendering.
  (renders
    (all         "heart <pack>      — all five teachings, six voices each")
    (one         "heart <pack> N    — one teaching across the six traditions")
    (witnessed   "golden rule in English · unity in Spanish · stillness in German —
                  the SAME numeric model speaking all three"))

  (invariant
    (the-shape-is-the-claim          six-voices-side-by-side-no-commentary-needed)
    (the-core-is-tradition-free      proven-by-band-a-community-authors-its-own-pack)
    (each-tradition-exceeds-the-shared  the-honesty-line-rides-in-every-rendering)
    (inference-not-measurement       the-lanes-stay-separate)
    (any-tongue-is-a-file            no-rebuild-ever)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to verify
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/shared-heart.fk \
#     form-stdlib/tests/shared-heart-band.fk      # → 31 three-way
#   bash scripts/shared_heart_demo.sh             # en/es/de from one numeric model
